status: MARC21-007: Level of compression of electronic resource
Kind of compression the electronic resource has been subjected to.

definition (en): Electronic resource has not been compressed through the use of any compression technique.

Lossless compression will allow an electronic resource to be compressed and decompressed with absolute fidelity each time. To be considered lossless, no informational loss may occur during this process.
scope note (en): An example of a lossless compression scheme would be TIFF Group 4 compression employed on bitonal image files.

definition (en): Lossy compression schemes employ techniques which average or discard some of the encoded digital information. When the file is decompressed, it will not be an exact replica of the original file.
scope note (en): Examples of lossy compression schemes include JPEG, and Kodak ImagePac (Photo CD), AC-3 (Dolby Digital) and MPEG.

definition (en): Mixture of techniques has been used to compress various parts of the electronic resource.
